The paper discusses the development of social media tools that aim to overcome censorship and Internet kill switches, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The tools also use Android devices for communication, which relates to networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also mentions enhancing privacy and anonymity, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and cryptography and security (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of these tools on the Internet, which relates to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
